glide time
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:originally, the ability with permission of one'ssuperiors to work one's own chosen hours within certain limits; later became synonym for taking life easy in the Public Service.

Flexible working hours allowing for varied starting and finishing times introduced to the State Services [check Brit., Aust flexitime]




Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: also gliding on
